016 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Awards|Choice TV Actress: Drama]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Awards|Choice TV: Chemistry]] {{small|(with [[Tyler Blackburn]])}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<center>2017</center>\n| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| [[People's Choice Awards|Favorite Cable TV Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[2017 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2017 Teen Choice Awards#Television|Choice TV Actress: Drama]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Ashley Benson}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{AllRovi name}}\n* [https://faviana.com/blog/celebrity-prom-dress-inspiration Ashley Benson spokesmodel for Faviana]\n\n{{Teen Choice Award Choice TV Actress Drama|state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Benson, Ashley}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Anaheim, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child models]]\n[[Category:American female dancers]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Dancers from California]]\n[[Category:Female models from California]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Orange County School of the Arts alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Anaheim Hills, California]]\n[[Category:LGBT models]]\n[[Category:LGBT actresses]]\n[[Category:LGBT dancers]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from California]]\n", "name_user": "TheRedundancy125", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashley_Benson"}
{"title_page": "Crystal Johnson (singer)", "text_new": "{{short description|singer, songwriter, producer, and actress from Brooklyn, NY}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Crystal Johnson  \n| image              = Crystal_Johnson.jpg\n| birth_name         = Crystal Jeanell Johnson\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Producer\n* Playright\n* Actress\n* Artist\n}}\n| website         = {{URL|crystaljohnson.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Crystal Jeanell Johnson''' is a singer, songwriter, producer, and actress originally from Brooklyn, New York.  Her career began at age 7, when she recorded with Pink Floyd and the Institutional Children's Choir, and has included a variety of stage productions and musical collaborations. She was cast in the lead role of the musical play \"Mama, I Want To Sing\" in 1983. She has worked with an array of well-known artists, including [[Usher (musician)|Usher]], [[Angie Stone]],<ref>{{cite AV media notes|\n|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/angie-stone/cinderella-ballin/7487027\n| title       = Stone Love\n| others      = Angie Stone; \"Cinderella Ballin\" Co-Writer, Vocalist\n| year        = 2004\n| type      = Vinyl or CD\n| publisher   = MCA\n}}</ref> [[Anthony Hamilton (musician)|Anthony Hamilton]],<ref>https://www.shazam.com/track/54114234/never-let-go</ref> [[Mobb Deep]],<ref> https://open.spotify.com/album/1cCAb1vN8uUsdfEylVmTLs?highlight=spotify:track:0Y1wsOHYGbNNNGeYjQJ8BL </ref> [[Heavy D]],<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Heavy-D-The-Boyz-Got-Me-Waiting/release/706978 </ref> [[Dr. Dre]],<ref>https://www.shazam.com/amp/track/230125/the-message </ref> and [[Pete Rock & CL Smooth]].<ref>\n{{cite web \n| title = Crystal Johnson Drops \"The Day Before Heaven\" \n| url = http://thehypemagazine.blogspot.com/2011/05/crystal-johnson-drops-day-before-heaven.html \n| work = The Hype Magazine\n| accessdate = 2011-11-13 \n }}\n</ref>\n\nCrystal's vocal credits include several albums that charted in the United States, including \"Got Me Waiting\" from [[Heavy D|Heavy D & the Boyz]]'s album ''[[Nuttin' but Love]]'',<ref>{{cite web \n| title = iTunes - Music - 20th Century Masters - The Millenium Collection: The Best of Heavy D & The Boyz by Heavy D & The Boyz \n| url = https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/20th-century-masters-the-millenium/id14310624 \n| accessdate = 2011-11-19  }}</ref> which topped the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' US Rap chart and reached #20 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], \"[[Take You There (Pete Rock & CL Smooth song)|Take You There]]\" from Pete Rock & CL Smooth's album ''[[The Main Ingredient (Pete Rock & CL Smooth album)|The Main Ingredient]]'', which reached #76 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, \"[[Temperature's Rising (Mobb Deep song)|Temperature's Rising]]\"<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JEtnfSidSAI</ref> from Mobb Deep's ''[[The Infamous]]'', which reached #3 on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart, and her vocal skills are exhibited on the remix of their single \"Survival of the Fittest\".<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cLNs0BCgt_Q</ref> Crystal contributed vocals on Usher's debut album ''[[Usher (album)|Usher]]'' which debuted at #187 on the US Billboard 200 chart <ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Usher_(album)</ref>.   Crystal is the vocalist on \"Lovin' You\"<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SVS2OULMfhI</ref> from the [[Who's the Man? (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for the film ''[[Who's the Man?]]''.<ref name=\"BllbrdAlbms\">{{cite web|last=|first=|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r169811|pure_url=yes}}|title=allmusic ((( Who's the Man? > Charts & Awards > Billboard Albums )))|format=|work=|publisher=Allmusic|accessdate=2011-11-19}}</ref>  She is also an arranger and lyricist for the album, which reached #8 on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart in 1993. In 1994, Crystal performed \"Take You There\" with [[Pete Rock & CL Smooth]] live on the Jon Stewart show.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-Kz6arjuFjc</ref> Crystal is featured on the single \"More of Me\" with [[Mike City]], released in 2015.<ref> https://play.google.com/music/preview/Tnostjvcvqla7legfur3yyk5xya?play=1 </ref>  \n\nCrystal co-wrote \u201cThe Message\u201d with [[Dr. Dre]] featuring [[Mary J. Blige]] on Dr. Dre\u2019s solo debut album ''[[The Chronic]]'',<ref> https://www.pandora.com/artist/credits/dr-dre/2001-explicit/the-message/TR4vVlPqp7ZkPlV</ref> \u201cNever Let Go\u201d with Anthony Hamilton from the album ''Back to Love'',<ref> https://www.pandora.com/artist/lyrics/anthony-hamilton/back-to-love-deluxe-version/never-let-go/TR59w6zbcdw7dkX</ref> and \u201cCinderella Ballin\u2019\u201d with [[Angie Stone]] from the studio album ''[[Stone Love]]''.<ref> https://www.pandora.com/artist/credits/angie-stone/stone-love/cinderella-ballin/TRxK796ZZ5x2wKk</ref>\n\nCrystal's self-produced album, released in 2011, is titled ''The Day Before Heaven''.<ref>{{cite web\n| title = Crystal Johnson (Artist Website)\n| url = http://www.crystaljohnson.com/#!\n| accessdate = 2011-11-13\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120322185306/http://www.crystaljohnson.com/#!\n| archive-date = 2012-03-22\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref> In 2016, Crystal wrote, produced, directed and starred in her autobiographical play ''The Day Before Heaven''.<ref>https://www.broadwayworld.com/brooklyn/article/Crystal-Johnsons-THE-DAY-BEFORE-HEAVEN-Musical-Comes-to-Brooklyn-20160428</ref>  \n\nCrystal is working on new material which is scheduled to be released in Spring of 2020. \n\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120322185306/http://www.crystaljohnson.com/ Crystal Johnson]\n* [http://www.soulinterviews.com/crystal-johnson-2012/ Crystal Johnson 2012 Audio Interview at Soulinterviews.com]\n*https://www.kickmag.net/2011/05/06/songbird-crystal-johnson-drops-debut-cd-the-day-before-heaven/\n*https://www.broadwayworld.com/brooklyn/article/Crystal-Johnsons-THE-DAY-BEFORE-HEAVEN-Musical-Comes-to-Brooklyn-20160428\n*http://honeycombartists.blogspot.com/2010/08/crystal-johnson-singersongwriterproduce.html\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n* ''The Day Before Heaven'' (2011)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johnson, Crystal}}\n[[Category:Singers from New York City]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American hip hop singers]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from New York (state)]]\n\n\n{{US-hiphop-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|singer, songwriter, producer, and actress from Brooklyn, NY}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Crystal Johnson  \n| image              = Crystal_Johnson.jpg\n| birth_name         = Crystal Jeanell Johnson\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Producer\n* Playright\n* Actress\n* Artist\n}}\n| website         = {{URL|crystaljohnson.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Crystal Jeanell Johnson''' is a singer, songwriter, producer, and actress originally from Brooklyn, New York.  Her career began at age 7, when she recorded with Pink Floyd and the Institutional Children's Choir, and has included a variety of stage productions and musical collaborations. She was cast in the lead role of the musical play \"Mama, I Want To Sing\" in 1983. She has worked with an array of well-known artists, including [[Usher (musician)|Usher]], [[Angie Stone]],<ref>{{cite AV media notes|\n|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/angie-stone/cinderella-ballin/7487027\n| title       = Stone Love\n| others      = Angie Stone; \"Cinderella Ballin\" Co-Writer, Vocalist\n| year        = 2004\n| type      = Vinyl or CD\n| publisher   = MCA\n}}</ref> [[Anthony Hamilton (musician)|Anthony Hamilton]],<ref>https://www.shazam.com/track/54114234/never-let-go</ref> [[Mobb Deep]],<ref> https://open.spotify.com/album/1cCAb1vN8uUsdfEylVmTLs?highlight=spotify:track:0Y1wsOH