3 Compilation (Pavement Music, 2000)\n*''The Best of Malevolent Creation'' (Roadrunner, 2003)\n*''Retrospective'' (Crash Music, 2005)\n*''Essentials'' (Crash Music, 2009)\n\n===DVD===\n*''Lost Commandments'' (Massacre Records, 2008) \u2013 It was an Arctic Music release that was licensed to Massacre Records for European release\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.metal-archives.com/bands/Malevolent_Creation/175 Malevolent Creation @ Encyclopaedia Metallum]\n*[http://thegrimoire.com/666/malevolent3/tabid/77/Default.aspx  Malevolent Creation @ Band interview]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Malevolent Creation}}\n\n[[Category:Century Media Records artists]]\n[[Category:Death metal musical groups from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1987]]\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2009}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Malevolent Creation\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| caption          = \n| origin           = [[Buffalo, New York]], United States\n| genre            = [[Death metal]]\n| years_active     = 1987\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Nuclear Blast]]\n* Pavement\n* [[Roadrunner Records|Roadrunner]]\n* [[Century Media Records|Century Media]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Demolition Hammer]]\n* [[Cannibal Corpse]]\n* [[Monstrosity (band)|Monstrosity]]\n* [[Hate Eternal]]\n* [[Nile (band)|Nile]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://label.agoniarecords.com/index.php?a=0NhEiQBw88lAHpRQgBf4v1j3i1WD48t0XYXvg9spPM0woA/3+wW6qQ==|title=Agonia Records|first=Piotr|last=Masztal|website=Label.agoniarecords.com|accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n| website          = {{Facebook|malevolentcreation}}\n| current_members  = * [[Phil Fasciana]]\n* Lee Wollenschlaeger\n* Josh Gibbs\n* Ron Parmer\n| past_members     = * Jim Nickles\n* Kyle Symons\n* Jeff Juszkiewicz\n* Ariel Alvarado\n* [[Rob Barrett]]\n* John Paul Soars\n* Gordon Sims\n* Marco Martell\n* Jon Rubin\n* Alex Marquez\n* Mark Simpson\n* [[Dave Culross]]\n* [[David Kinkade]]\n* [[Derek Roddy]]\n* Fabian Aguirre\n* [[Brett Hoffman]]\n* Jason Blachowicz\n* Justin DiPinto\n* Gio Geraca\n* Phil Cancilla\n}}\n'''Malevolent Creation''' is an American [[death metal]] band formed in [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], New York in 1987.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Malevolent Creation - Encyclopaedia Metallum: The Metal Archives|url = http://www.metal-archives.com/bands/Malevolent_Creation/175|website = www.metal-archives.com|accessdate = 2015-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = The BNR Metal Pages - Band|url = http://www.bnrmetal.com/v3/band/band/MaCr|website = Bnrmetal.com|accessdate = 2015-10-21|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170723123840/http://www.bnrmetal.com/v3/band/band/MaCr|archive-date = 2017-07-23|url-status = dead}}</ref> The band's original members were vocalist Brett Hoffmann, guitarists Phil Fasciana (born January 1, 1967) and Jim Nickles, bassist Jason Blachowicz, and drummer Dennis Kubas. Phil Fasciana was the only founding member who stayed with the band consistently.<ref>{{Cite web|title = METALLIAN - Malevolent Creation|url = http://www.metallian.com/malevolentcreation.php|website = Metallian.com|accessdate = 2015-10-22}}</ref>\n\nThe band moved to [[Florida]] a year after it formed, and they became a part of the emergent local death metal scene, landing a deal with [[Roadrunner Records]] and helping to develop the \"Florida Death Metal\" sound.<ref>{{Cite book|title = Death Metal Music: The Passion and Politics of a Subculture|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=kyeSCgAAQBAJ|publisher = McFarland|date = 2003-05-05|isbn = 9780786415854|language = en|first = Natalie J.|last = Purcell}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title = Death Metal Music: The Passion and Politics of a Subculture|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=AwJJR5vvlIsC|publisher = McFarland|date = 2003-05-05|isbn = 9780786484065|language = en|first = Natalie J.|last = Purcell}}</ref> In 1991 their debut album, ''[[The Ten Commandments (Malevolent Creation album)|The Ten Commandments]]'', became something of a landmark in the death metal underground, expanding on the early work of bands such as [[Slayer]], [[Kreator]], [[Possessed (band)|Possessed]], [[Onslaught (band)|Onslaught]], [[Obituary (band)|Obituary]] and [[Death (metal band)|Death]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Steve Huey |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/malevolent-creation-mn0000668265/biography |title=Malevolent Creation &#124; Biography |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |date= |accessdate=2015-08-01}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nMalevolent Creation signed a management deal with Extreme Management Group ([[Suffocation (band)|Suffocation]], [[Origin (band)|Origin]]) in 2010 and announced April 5, 2010 as the starting date for recording their next album with Erik Rutan at Mana Recording Studios (Cannibal Corpse, Vital Remains, Goatwhore, etc.)<ref name=\"a1159\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nuclearblastusa.com/nb/v2/news/news.php?newsID=1159 |title=News |publisher=Nuclear Blast USA |date=2015-07-28 |accessdate=2015-08-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = News - Nuclear Blast USA|url = http://www.nuclearblastusa.com/nb/v2/news/news.php?newsID=1159|website = Nuclearblastusa.com|accessdate = 2015-10-21}}</ref> The band released the following statement:\n\n\"After over 20 years in existence, and now having the most solid line up in years, we really wanted to make sure that with this new album we elevated the band in every way. Getting good management was crucial and EMG has a great track record. Erik has been talking to us since [[Doomsday X]] to record us, and with Gus Rios (Drums) being in the band full time now, we didn't want him to have the responsibility of producing the album as well as writing and playing. Erik really understands what we are about, and has all of the same thoughts about recording as us. It really couldn't be a better working situation. We've said it before but this album really is without a doubt is the most relentless, focused and brutal MALEVOLENT CREATION album ever! We really went back to our roots, not only as a band, but as fans of metal. We wrote an album of songs that we as fans of brutal music would want to hear.\"<ref name=\"a1159\" />\n\nOn October 15, 2014, Malevolent Creation announced that they signed a worldwide record deal with [[Century Media Records]]. In 2015, they released their 12th studio album, Dead Man's Path, on Century Media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centurymedia.com/newsdetailed.aspx?IdNews=15022&IdCompany=3 |title=MALEVOLENT CREATION signs worldwide deal with Century Media Records |publisher=[[Century Media Records]] |date=October 15, 2014 |accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = METALLIAN - Malevolent Creation|url = http://www.metallian.com/malevolentcreation.php|website = Metallian.com|accessdate = 2015-10-21}}</ref> In September 2016, it was reported that the band had broke up following the cancellation of their upcoming U.S. tour, and departure of their long-time bassist Jason Blachowicz.<ref>{{cite web|title = Malevolent Creation Reportedly Breaks Up|url = http://www.metalunderground.com/news/details.cfm?newsid=127566|website=Metalunderground.com |date=September 18, 2016}}</ref> Phil Fasciana is the only remaining member left.\n\nOn November 29, 2017, it was announced that Malevolent Creation has returned with a new lineup, and an upcoming album to be released next year.<ref>{{cite web|title=MALEVOLENT CREATION Announces New Lineup; 13th Album Due In 2018|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/malevolent-creation-announces-new-lineup-13th-album-due-in-2018/|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=November 29, 2017|date=November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2018, original vocalist Brett Hoffmann died from colon cancer at the age of 51.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former MALEVOLENT CREATION Singer BRET HOFFMANN Dead At 51|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/former-malevolent-creation-singer-bret-hoffmann-dead-at-51/|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=July 7, 2018|date=July 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Current lineup===\n*Phil Fasciana \u2013 [[rhythm guitar]] (1987\u2013present)\n*Josh Gibbs \u2013 [[Bass guitar|bass]] (2017\u2013present)\n*Ryan Taylor \u2013 [[Death growl|vocals]], [[lead guitar]] (2020\u2013present)\n*Ronnie Parmer \u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]] (2020\u2013present)\n\n===Live members===\n*[[Peter T\u00e4gtgren]] \u2013 lead guitar (1988)\n*Ariel Alvarado \u2013 drums (2002\u20132003)\n*[[David Kinkade]] \u2013 drums (2006) \n*Sean Martinez \u2013 bass (2011)\n*John Cooke \u2013 bass (2011\u20132012)\n*James Walford \u2013 lead guitar (2011)\n*Kevin Peace \u2013 bass (2013)\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Former members===\n*[[Brett Hoffmann]] \u2013 vocals (1987\u20131993, 1998\u20132001, 2006\u20132016; died 2018)\n*Mark Simpson \u2013 drums (1987\u20131991)\n*Jon Rubin \u2013 lead guitar (1987\u20131990, 1993\u20131996, 2005\u20132008) \n*Mark van Erp \u2013 bass (1987\u20131990) \n*Jason Blachowicz \u2013 bass (1987, 1991\u20131997, 2005\u20132007, 2010\u20132016), vocals (1995\u20131997)\n*Dennis Kubas \u2013 drums (1987)\n*Jim Nickles \u2013 lead guitar (1987) \n*Lee Harrison \u2013 drums (1989) \n*Jeff Juszkiewicz \u2013 guitars (1991) \n*Alex Marquez \u2013 drums (1992\u20131994) \n*[[Rob Barrett]] \u2013 lead guitar (1992\u20131993, 1998\u20132005) \n*Larry Hawke \u2013 drums (1993; died 1997) \n*[[Dave Culross]] \u2013 drums (1995, 1998\u20132001, 2003\u20132004, 2007) \n*[[Derek Roddy]] \u2013 drums (1996\u20131997) \n*John Paul Soars \u2013 lead guitar (1997) \n*Gordon Sims \u2013 bass (1998\u20132005)\n*Kyle Symons \u2013 vocals (2001\u20132006)\n*Justin DiPinto \u2013 drums (2002\u20132003, 2014\u20132016)\n*[[Tony Laureano]] \u2013 drums (2003) \n*Marco Martell \u2013 bass (2007\u20132008), lead guitar (2007\u20132010) \n*Fabian Aguirre \u2013 drums (2007\u20132010)\n*Gus Rios \u2013 drums (2007, 2010\u20132014)\n*Gio Geraca \u2013 lead guitar (2009\u20132016)\n*Lee Wollenschlaeger \u2013 vocals, lead guitar (2017\u20132020)\n*Phil Cancilla \u2013 drums (2017\u20132020)\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Timeline===\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize = width:750 height:auto barincrement:19\nPlotArea = left:120 bottom:90 top:5 right:10\nAlignbars = justify\nDateFormat  = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod = from:01/01/1987 till:{{#time: m/d/Y }}\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\nLegend = orientation:vertical position:bottom columns:4\nScaleMajor = increment:2 start:1987\nScaleMinor = increment:1 start:1988\n\nColors =\n id:vocals  value:red                legend:Vocals\n id:lead    value:teal               legend:Lead_guitar\n id:rhythm  value:brightgreen        legend:Rhythm_guitar\n id:bass    value:blue               legend:Bass\n id:drums   value:orange             legend:Drums\n id:album   value:black              legend:Studio_album\n \nLineData =\n  at:04/24/1991 color:album layer:back\n  at:04/01/1992 color:album layer:back\n  at:10/26/1993 color:album layer:back\n  at:05/23/1995 color:album layer:back\n  at:06/24/1997 color:album layer:back\n  at:10/27/1998 color:album layer:back\n  at:10/17/2000 color:album layer:back\n  at:11/11/2002 color:album layer:back\n  at:06/28/2004 color:album layer:back\n  at:07/17/2007 color:album layer:back\n  at:08/24/2010 color:album layer:back\n  at:10/02/2015 color:album layer:back\n  at:01/18/2019 color:album layer:back\n \nBarData = \n  bar:Brett     text:\"Brett Hoffman\"\n  bar:Kyle      text:\"Kyle Symons\"\n  bar:LeeW      text:\"Lee Wollenschlaeger\"\n  bar:Ryan      text:\"Ryan Taylor\"\n  bar:Jim       text:\"Jim Nickles\"\n  bar:Jon       text:\"Jon Rubin\"\n  bar:Jeff      text:\"Jeff Juszkiewicz\"\n  bar:Rob       text:\"Rob Barrett\"\n  bar:JP        text:\"John Paul Soars\"\n  bar:Phil      text:\"Phil Fasciana\"\n  bar:Jason     text:\"Jason Blachowicz\"\n  bar:Mark      text: